						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall of the central shrine, Āmalakēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Rājarāja III. Year 20: 1235-36 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription seems to refer to some grant of land for food-offerings to god Iḷaiyapiḷḷaiyār (Subrahmaṇya) by a certain Maṟaiñāṉasambandar.</p>						

						</summary>
